notes: Bonus 100.00 for top Cat 3 ride provide by Mike Underwood Memorial Fund.

title: Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey
description:
Big time MTB racing continues with the 3rd Annual Bone Bender 3/6 Hour MTB Odyssey.  Come enjoy some of the sweetest and challenging trails in the Midwest. Party with your friends and have a grand old time riding your bike. 
You can chose either 3 or 6 hours of FUN. Solo and Team classes are available.
course: We move the BB36 to Clinton Lake State Park for 2011. We have over 20 miles of trails to make this years event very fun and challenging. The trails at Clinton are single track, dirt trails exhibiting rocks, tree roots, creek crossings and rolling hills.
registration:
Online registration is available at www.bikereg.com. 
Race day registration/pack pick-up opens at 8:00 am and closes 30 minutes before race time.
notes:
Annual or daily vehicle permit required ($4.20)
Camping is available for both tent and camper
All Pre-Registered Riders are guaranteed an event t-shirt/One raffle ticket/Post Race Dinner
For more information call 816.200.1273 or 816.455.2453
directions: Directions: I-70 – take from KC (traveling West), past both Lawrence exits, to Exit #197 –the Lecompton exit.  (There will be a brown sign with white letters that says Clinton & Perry Lake) After paying toll, take a left at the stop sign.  This is 10 Hwy East take it to the Clinton Parkway exit (3RD Exit after exiting I 70 on 10 hwy) at the bottom of the Exit Ramp turn right at the stop sign  (you will be facing E900 Road), take another right at the dead end, then take the second left this is our entrance to the State Park.  Follow the long drive, it goes down a hill then up a hill to the pay booth. Proceed to campground #3 which is the 6th left after passing the park office.

title: Joseph Sheehan Road Race
description: 52 mile Road Race from Leavenworth to Atchison and back.  Fully supported. Lead and wheel vehicles for each category.  Neutral SAG just before Atchison.
course: Course starts at the Metropolitan Steak House.  Follow Santa Fe Trails Road to Lowemont.  Road continues as Millwood Road to Atchison.  Follow US 73 back to Lowemont. Take Santa Fe Trails Road to finish atop Government Hill. Juniors race for thirty miles and finish in Atchison
registration: Register online at USAC.  Registration also available at Santa Fe Trails Bicycle Shop.  On site registration at Metropolitan Steak House from 7 AM to 8:15 AM.
notes: All USAC Rules apply.  CPSC Approved Helmets are required at all times.  Promoter reserves right to adjust start times,distances, alter courses, cancel and combine categories and prize list on day of race. This race is part of the KBAR and KBAT series and awards 1.5 x KBAR and KBAT points. Winners of the 2010 KBAR will receive free entry. Fees include $1.00 KCA and $3.00 USAC insurance fee.  Online registration closes April 29.  USAC license is required.  One day licenses are available at the registration table. On Site registration closes at 8:15 AM.  Wheel vehicle will be provided.  Registration will be held at the Metropolitan Steak House.  Awards dinner will be at the Metropolitan Steak House beginning at 12:30 PM.  Course is 52 miles, uphill finish, and signed.  Sweeper vehicle and radio net will be provided.  Contacts 913 682-2444 913 306-3016 sheebhans@aol.com www.santafebikes.com
directions: From Kansas City, Lawrence or Topeka. Take I70 to the Bonner Springs exit.  Take K7 north for 16 miles.  Turn left (west) on Metropolitan.  Go one mile to the Metropolitan Steak House on left.

title: Late Night Under the Lights
description: Santa Fe Trails Bike Racing Series.  There will be a children\'s ride preceding the adult racing.  The adults will race three (3) times. The races will include \"Devil takes the Hindmost,\"  \"Win and Out,\" and a four (4) lap scratch race.
course: The ride will be a .6 mile loop on clean pavement at the Warren Middle School.  It will be closed to traffic.
registration: On-site registration begins at 6:15 pm.  Racers may register at Santa Fe Trails Bike Shop during normal business hours.
notes: This will be multiple laps on a closed course.  No cars will be allowed while the event is ongoing.  A helmet is required to ride.  USA Cycling license required.  One-day licenses will be available on-site.
directions: Warren Middle School can be found by taking 10th street to limit.  Take Limit west to New Lawrence road.  Turn left onto New Lawrence road and follow to the school.

title: Tour de Lizard Fat Tire Classic (10th Annual&
Manions CX
description: One of Kansas City\'s premier cyclocross events including all collegiate categories.
registration: Registration Registration opens at 11:30 a.m. on 9/24 and at 8:30 a.m. on 9/25.  Registration for each race closes thirty minutes prior to the race\'s start time.  Online registration closes at 11:00 PM on 9/22.  Entry fee for same day second race is $10.  .
notes: All USAC rules apply.  A USAC license is required to race.  One day licenses are available for $10 at registration.  CPSC approved helmets must be worn at all times on a moving bike.  Mountain bikes are allowed but must have the bar ends removed.  Events held regardless of inclement weather.  Entry fee includes $3.00 USAC insurance fee and $1.00 KCA fee.
directions: From Leavenworth Road, go north on 67th st., just keep going, don\'t stop until you see a big field and a barn, please park where the parking signs permit you to.
